# NOTE: This file is NOT used by GitHub Pages (GitHub ignores _headers).
# It is kept for Netlify/Cloudflare Pages if you migrate hosting later.
# For GitHub Pages, equivalent headers are set via <meta> tags in the HTML files.
# GitHub Pages already provides Strict-Transport-Security and X-Content-Type-Options.
/*
  Referrer-Policy: no-referrer
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Permissions-Policy: accelerometer=(), camera=(), geolocation=(), gyroscope=(), magnetometer=(), microphone=(), payment=(), usb=()
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload